1. System Overview
🔹 Problem Definition

Customer support teams handle repetitive queries from large documentation (FAQs, manuals, policies). Traditional bots fail because:

They don’t use updated knowledge
They hallucinate answers
They lack escalation mechanisms
🔹 Proposed Solution

A RAG-based Customer Support Assistant that:

Reads a PDF knowledge base
Retrieves relevant chunks using embeddings
Generates contextual answers using LLM
Uses LangGraph workflow for decision-making
Escalates complex queries via Human-in-the-Loop (HITL)
🔹 Scope

✔ Single PDF knowledge base
✔ Query answering
✔ Intent-based routing
✔ HITL escalation
❌ No multilingual / voice (future scope)

