3. Component Description
📄 Document Loader
Loads PDF using PyPDFLoader
Extracts raw text
✂️ Chunking Strategy
Recursive Character Splitter
Chunk size: 500–1000 tokens
Overlap: 100–200 tokens
🧠 Embedding Model
Example: sentence-transformers/all-MiniLM-L6-v2
Converts text → vectors
🗄 Vector Store
ChromaDB
Stores embeddings + metadata
Enables similarity search
🔍 Retriever
Top-K retrieval (k=3 or 5)
Cosine similarity
🤖 LLM
Example: OpenAI / Groq / LLaMA
Generates final answer
🔁 Graph Workflow Engine
LangGraph
Controls flow using nodes & edges
🎯 Routing Layer
Decides:
Answer directly
Escalate to human
👨‍💻 HITL Module
Sends query to human agent
Integrates human response

4. Data Flow
📥 Ingestion Flow
PDF → Loader → Chunking → Embeddings → ChromaDB
📤 Query Flow
User Query → Embed → Retrieve chunks → LLM → Response
🔄 Full Lifecycle
User asks question
Query embedded
Relevant chunks retrieved
LLM generates answer
Confidence evaluated
If low → HITL escalation

5. Technology Choices
Why ChromaDB?
Lightweight
Easy local setup
Fast similarity search
Why LangGraph?
Stateful workflows
Supports branching logic
Ideal for HITL systems
LLM Choice
OpenAI GPT / LLaMA / Groq
Trade-off: cost vs performance


6. Scalability Considerations
📈 Large Documents
Incremental indexing
Batch embedding
⚡ High Query Load
Caching layer
Async processing
⏱ Latency
Reduce chunk size
Use smaller embedding model
